.env
generated/
__pycache__/
*.pyc
.pio/
build/
*.elf
*.bin
*.csv
*.log
node_modules/
dist/
.venv/
.venv*/
venv/
.pytest_cache/
*.egg-info/
.claude/settings.local.json

# The golden corpus (issue #4) is committed reference data produced ONLY by
# scripts/export_golden.py. The globs above (*.csv, and formerly *.log) would
# otherwise swallow its files, so re-include the whole corpus tree. Everything
# under it is intentional and byte-checked in CI; never hand-edit it.
!tests/golden_corpus/**

# The build-benchmark harness (issue #107) lives in directories literally named
# `build`, which the `build/` ignore above (meant for compiled firmware/artifacts)
# would otherwise swallow. Re-include these committed SOURCE trees — the harness
# code, its mock CI test, and the build_specs corpus README's golden dir. Only the
# directory itself must be re-included for git to descend into it.
!packages/agent/bench/build/
!packages/agent/bench/build/**
!packages/agent/tests/build/
!packages/agent/tests/build/**
